In [5]:
def min_max_scale(x, new_min=0, new_max=255, dtype='float32', return_stats=False):
    mn, mx = np.min(x), np.max(x)
    res = (x - mn)/(mx - mn+1e-4)
    res = (res * (new_max - new_min) + new_min).astype(dtype)
    if return_stats:
        return res, mn, mx
    return res

def equalize_hist(x):
    out = cv2.equalizeHist(
        min_max_scale(x, 0, 255, 'uint8')
    )
    return out

In [7]:
def naive_model(optimizer):
    model = tf.keras.Sequential([
        tf.keras.layers.Input(shape=[487, 458, 1]),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(
            filters=24, kernel_size=3, activation="elu", kernel_initializer="he_normal", padding='same'
        ),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(
            filters=48, kernel_size=5, activation="elu", kernel_initializer="he_normal", padding='same'
        ),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(
            filters=48, kernel_size=7, activation="elu", kernel_initializer="he_normal", padding='same'
        ),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(
            filters=48, kernel_size=5, activation="elu", kernel_initializer="he_normal", padding='same'
        ),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(
            filters=48, kernel_size=5, activation="elu", kernel_initializer="he_normal", padding='same'
        ),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(
            filters=24, kernel_size=5, activation="elu", kernel_initializer="he_normal", padding='same'
        ),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(
            filters=1, kernel_size=3, activation="elu", kernel_initializer="he_normal", padding='same'
        ),
    ])
    model.compile(optimizer, loss='mse')
    return model
